<DEEP_SCAN_V3>
@ID: HTTP_SECURITY_HEADERS_AUDIT
@GOAL: VERIFY_IMPLEMENTATION_OF_PROTECTIVE_HTTP_HEADERS
@PARENT_CONTEXT: network_infra.protocol, entry_points.protocol

<EXECUTION_PIPELINE>
1. MIDDLEWARE_HEADER_SCAN: Найти библиотеки типа `helmet` или `django-csp`.
2. CSP_STRICTNESS_ANALYSIS: Проверка на `unsafe-inline` и `unsafe-eval`.
3. INFRA_SYNC: Сопоставить заголовки кода с Nginx/Cloudflare из Discovery.
4. SCENARIO_GENERATION: Описать сценарий XSS или Clickjacking при отсутствии конкретного заголовка.

   - HYBRID_ANALYSIS: Read JSON artifacts (syft.json, grype.json, kics.json) from .security_review/artifacts/raw_tools_output/. Treat these results as 'Hard Evidence'. Perform AI Reachability Analysis to verify if the vulnerable component is reachable from the code. If confirmed, elevate the finding status to BLOCKER.
</EXECUTION_PIPELINE>

<OUTPUT_SPEC>
# ФОРМАТ ДЛЯ АВТОМАТИЧЕСКОГО ПАРСИНГА БЭКЕНДОМ
🚨 FINDING [http_headers_audit]:
FILE: [MAIN_APP_FILE_OR_INFRA_CONFIG]
LINE: [NUM]
CODE: [HEADER_SETTING_OR_MIDDLEWARE]
DESCRIPTION: [Tool_Name] found [Vulnerability_ID]. AI Analysis confirmed that the vulnerable path is active in the current code flow via [Function_Name].
SCENARIO_OF_ATTACK: An attacker exploits the absence of [HEADER] to perform a [ATTACK_TYPE] (e.g., XSS via missing CSP or Clickjacking via missing X-Frame-Options), targeting users in their browser context.
@ANALYTICS_DATA: {"domain": "INFRA", "impact": 0.6}
VISUALIZE: "Image of a browser security model showing how headers block attack vectors."
</OUTPUT_SPEC>
</DEEP_SCAN_V3>